<!-- 
    TABBED PROFILE CODE
    BY PANDAPPUCCINO
    
    == WHAT IS THIS? ==
    There are so many codes that I like certain parts of, but don't use the full scope of, so I decided to challenge myself to make this.  It's a full profile code with individual tabs (each tab is pre-coded with its own layout, but you can change them however you want!) that covers the basics of a character: their basic info, story, inventory, abilities, relationships, and design.  It also has a ribbon case (inspired by the Modular Layout by CivilEngideer found at https://toyhou.se/6489004.modular-customizable-layout) and can be expanded to include whatever you want.
    
    This code is heavily inspired by the aforementioned CivilEngideer and also by Aurorean.  Please give them a visit if you like this code!
    
    == HOW DO I USE IT? ==
    Just edit each section as needed!  There are comments to clarify each part for you.
    
    == WHAT'S THE CATCH? ==
    Just keep my credit intact; that's all I ask.
    
    == COMMON EDITING TIPS ==
    1) You can change the particular Bootstrap colors by replacing the color classes (such as bg-dark).  If you would prefer to remove the Bootstrap colors and use your own colors, just remove the entire color class and, in the given "style" section, add "background:" followed by a color, either a hex color or rgb/rgba value.
    2) You can remove the capitalization of the titles by removing the "text-uppercase" class from a given section.
    3) You can use inline color styling by using <span></span> tags in tandem with either Bootstrap color classes or custom color styling.
    4) You can adjust the width of the <hr> dividers (or any other element with the Bootstrap classes) by replacing the "w-75" class with another number.  For more precise styling, you can remove the class and style the widths directly; however, they may not look as good on mobile screens!
    5) You can adjust the color of the borders for some headers by changing the rgba() values; by default they are rgba(255,255,255,0.25), meaning a white border at 25% opacity.
	
-->

